Setup and Experiment
Instructions for
Fixed Device: Android
Mobile Device: iPhone/iPad
Overview of Tasks:
1. Install and setup the android app on the fixed device
2. Install and setup the iOS app on the mobile device
3. Perform the experiments as per the instructions in
the video attached towards the end
● Download .apk file (download link,
alternately scan the QR code above)
● Tap “Install”
Android App Installation (1)
● Tap “Allow from this source” if you are
installing via the QR code, otherwise
continue ahead
Android App Installation (2)
● Tap “Install Anyway” and “Don’t
Send” in the subsequent window
Android App Installation (3)
● Continue to “Open” the app.
Android App Installation (4)
● Open the app you’ve just installed.
● Grant the required permissions and turn
bluetooth on
● Tap “Transmit Beacons”
Set up Fixed Device (1)
● Toggle the switch to begin transmitting
Set up fixed device (2)
● Take note of device name and generated
QR Code. This will be scanned after
experiments are done (not now)
Set up fixed device (3)
iOS App Installation (1)
● Before you start make sure your phone is updated to
iOS 13.4.1 Software.
● Download Testflight from App Store. (Download
Link)
● Open this Link in Testflight:
https://testflight.apple.com/join/LWw7Hz8x
Or equivalently scan the QR code on the top
● Tap Install and Open the app
iOS App Installation (2)
Set up Mobile Device (1)
● Install the app as per earlier instructions on
your mobile iOS device.
● Open the app and grant access to the
permissions required
● Turn on your Bluetooth
● Tap “Scan for Beacons”
● Select your fixed android device name from
the screen. The device name would be the
name which showed up while setting up
your fixed device
Please see the video in the next slide to get
details on how to conduct the experiments
